eristic forenames:  French Alphonse, Chantal, Dominique, Francois, Herve, Michel, Rodolphe, Serge.","French (<b>Fouché</b>): variant of   Foucher  . Compare   Fooshee  ,   Foshee  ,   Fouch  , and   Foushee  .","Altered form (<b>Fouché</b>) of French   Foucher   (compare 1 above), found mainly in South Africa."],"variants":[{"name":"Foucher","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Etienne, Henri, Lydie, Marcel, Rosaire.","French: from the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Folchari</i>, composed of the elements <i>folk</i>, <i>folc</i> ‘people’ and <i>hari</i> ‘army’. Compare   Faucher   2."]},{"name":"Foushee","meanings":["Americanized form of French <b>Fouché</b> (see   Fouche   1).","History: This surname is listed in the (US) National Huguenot Society's register of qualified Huguenot ancestors (along with its original form <i>Fouché</i>) and also in the similar register of the Huguenot Society of America."]},{"name":"Fooshee","meanings":["Americanized form of French <b>Fouché</b> (see   Fouche   1)."]},{"name":"Foshee","meanings":["Americanized form of French <b>Fouché</b> (see   Fouche   1)."]},{"name":"Fouch","meanings":["Altered form of French <b>Fouché</b> (see   Fouche   1).","Altered form of   Fouts  , a surname of German origin.","English (of Norman origin): variant of   Fudge  ."]}]},{"name":"Isabella","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   Isabel  , which has been popular in England since the 18th century and has recently become the preferred form of the name."],"variants":[{"name":"Isobella","meanings":["Originally a Spanish version of   Elizabeth  , which was coined by deletion of the first syllable and alteration of the final consonant sound to one that can normally end a word in Spanish. The name was imported into France in the early Middle Ages, and thence into England. It was a royal name, and its enduring popularity may have been enhanced by the fact that it was borne by a queen of England—  Isabella  (  1296–1358 ), daughter of  Philip IV  of France—even though she led a turbulent life and eventually had her husband,  Edward II , murdered."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Isabella Zouche was born in 1532, in England, United Kingdom, her father, Baron Henricus Zouche, was 32 and her mother, Mrs Zouch, was 11529. She married John Millard in 1549, in Bath, Somerset, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in 1583, in Sussex, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 51."},"et":{"1532–1583":"1532–1583","1550–1583":"1550–1583","1515–1564":"1515–1564","1550–1592":"1550–1592","1500–1554":"1500–1554","1515–Female":"1515–Surnud","8 April 1550":"8. aprill 1550","1500":"1500","1532":"1532","1554":"1554","28 September 1564":"28. september 1564","1564":"1564","1583":"1583","1550":"1550","1592":"1592","1549":"1549","1515":"1515","Bath, Somerset, England":"Bath, Somerset, England","Horsham, Sussex, England":"Horsham, Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","St. Clement, Cornwall, England":"St Clement, Cornwall, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Kingdom of England (United Kingdom of Great Britain &amp; Northern Ireland)":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bath, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Bath, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Sussex, England, United Kingdom":"Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1532–1583":"1532–1583","1550–1583":"1550–1583","1515–1564":"1515–1564","1550–1592":"1550–1592","1500–1554":"1500–1554","1515–Female":"1515–Kuollut","8 April 1550":"8. huhtikuuta 1550","1500":"1500","1532":"1532","1554":"1554","28 September 1564":"28. syyskuuta 1564","1564":"1564","1583":"1583","1550":"1550","1592":"1592","1549":"1549","1515":"1515","Bath, Somerset, England":"Bath, Somerset, England","Horsham, Sussex, England":"Horsham, Sussex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","St. Clement, Cornwall, England":"St Clement, Cornwall, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Kingdom of England 